# NC Program Generator — Development Rules

## Core principles
- Safety first. Treat every G/M code related change as machine-impacting.
- Prioritize working behavior and correctness over explanations.
- Keep responses concise and result-focused unless detail is requested.

## Change guardrails
- Diff-first: present targeted edits, avoid full-file rewrites unless required.
- Ask before changing proprietary calculation logic or G/M code definitions.
- After each accepted change, include a short verification checklist:
  - What to confirm in simulator or on machine
  - Edge cases that could silently break output

## Managed files
- Shell: `index.html`
- Assets: `assets/style.css`, `assets/data.js`, `assets/app.js`, `assets/i18n.js`
- Templates under `テンプレート/`: `data_template_*.js`
- Helper script: `scripts/build-tonbo-templates-from-refs.mjs`

## Project-specific knowledge
- M408 = machining completion signal sent to external equipment (NCL044 only)
- M61 = machining completion signal (NCL012 only)
- NCL085 has no machining completion signal; output is intentionally empty
- G/M code roles differ by machine; do not assume standard behavior
- Template placeholders use `{{key}}` and are resolved at generation time
